<div class="page" id="page-medical"><canvas class="page-bg-canvas" id="bg-canvas-medical"></canvas>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="section-tag" data-reveal>What is Medical Thermography</div>
    <h1 class="display-h2" data-reveal data-delay="1">The science of<br><em>seeing heat.</em></h1>
    <p class="body-p" style="max-width:600px;margin-top:24px;" data-reveal data-delay="2">Medical thermography is a non-invasive clinical imaging technique that measures and maps the body's own heat emissions. When physiology changes, heat changes. Thermography makes those changes visible.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="medical-intro-grid">
    <div data-reveal="left">
      <div class="thermal-visual">
        <div class="thermal-scale"></div>
        <div class="thermal-label">THERMAL MAP · ANTERIOR VIEW</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fda-strip">
        <div class="fda-badge-circle">FDA<br>510k</div>
        <div class="fda-strip-text">
          <strong>FDA Class I Medical Device — Cleared</strong>
          <span>Same classification as stethoscopes and blood pressure monitors. No diagnostic claims. No liability exposure. Our clearance is under 8 years old.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div data-reveal="right">
      <div class="section-tag">How it works</div>
      <h2 class="display-h3" style="margin-bottom:24px;">From voltage<br>to <em>visible insight.</em></h2>
      <p class="body-p" style="margin-bottom:20px;">The thermographic camera does not "see" cancer or inflammation or any state of disease. It senses voltage — converted to temperature — converted to a sensed thermal image. The device has no opinion or judgment. It just conveys genuine information.</p>
      <p class="body-p" style="margin-bottom:20px;">Our challenge is purely human: to understand the thermodynamics of the body and how that relates to various physiological conditions. The thermal image is our reference — partly science, partly the art of practicing preventive medicine.</p>
      <p class="body-p">Representing thermography as a "Discovery Tool" is a concept most people can relate to — and it is within FDA Class I Branding and Labeling guidelines.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="process-section">
    <div class="section-tag" data-reveal>The Process</div>
    <h2 class="display-h3" data-reveal data-delay="1">Three steps from<br><em>scan to insight.</em></h2>
    <div class="process-steps">
      <div class="process-step" data-reveal data-delay="1">
        <div class="step-connector"></div>
        <div class="step-num">01</div>
        <div class="step-title">Infrared Sensors Detect Heat</div>
        <p class="step-desc">Every cell produces heat as a byproduct of metabolism. A high-resolution FLIR infrared camera passively detects the heat radiating from the body's surface — no contact, no radiation, no risk whatsoever.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step" data-reveal data-delay="2">
        <div class="step-connector"></div>
        <div class="step-num">02</div>
        <div class="step-title">TotalVision Maps Temperature</div>
        <p class="step-desc">Med-Hot's proprietary TotalVision software translates raw infrared data into a full-color thermal map. Multiple palettes reveal different temperature ranges, allowing trained thermographers to visualize patterns across the entire body.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step" data-reveal data-delay="3">
        <div class="step-num">03</div>
        <div class="step-title">Patterns Reveal Physiology</div>
        <p class="step-desc">Asymmetries, hot spots, and cold zones correspond to underlying physiological activity — inflammation, vascular changes, nerve involvement, and more — giving practitioners a non-invasive window into the body's living function.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="inflammation-section">
    <div class="section-tag" data-reveal>Thermography & Inflammation</div>
    <h2 class="display-h3" data-reveal data-delay="1">The most consequential<br>of all human <em>conditions.</em></h2>
    <div class="inflammation-grid">
      <div data-reveal="left">
        <p class="body-p" style="margin-bottom:20px;">Those who say "thermography cannot detect cancer" don't understand that detection of cancer was never the point. The device has no opinion or judgment — it just conveys genuine information.</p>
        <p class="body-p" style="margin-bottom:20px;">The computer makes it possible for us to measure and observe — with our eyes — the indisputable signs of inflammation. Inflammation is the acknowledged root of all chronic disease.</p>
        <p class="body-p" style="margin-bottom:20px;">Detection of cancer presumes cancer is already manifested. Detection of inflammation presumes an atypical anomaly — creating blood profusion in a specific region — that deserves attention before disease manifests.</p>
        <p class="body-p"><strong style="color:var(--white);">Ask yourself:</strong> which is of the most value to the assessment of an individual's physiological health?</p>
        <div class="compliance-note" style="margin-top:28px;">
          <p><strong>FDA Compliance note:</strong> Thermography cameras sense temperature variations — like blood pressure monitors sense pressure — but cannot independently make a diagnosis. All public marketing must represent thermography as a "Discovery Tool" within Class I Branding and Labeling guidelines.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div data-reveal="right">
        <div style="background:var(--deep);border:1px solid var(--border);padding:clamp(32px,4vw,48px);">
          <div class="section-tag" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Discovery vs Detection</div>
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0;">
            <div style="padding:20px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
              <div style="font-size:.65rem;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gray);margin-bottom:8px;font-weight:300;">Detection (Cancer)</div>
              <div style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.4;">Presumes cancer already exists. Reactive. Structural. After the fact.</div>
            </div>
            <div style="padding:20px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
              <div style="font-size:.65rem;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber);margin-bottom:8px;font-weight:300;">Discovery (Inflammation)</div>
              <div style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--white);line-height:1.4;">Presumes an atypical anomaly creating unusual blood profusion that deserves attention — before disease manifests.</div>
            </div>
            <div style="padding:20px 0;">
              <div style="font-size:.65rem;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--copper);margin-bottom:8px;font-weight:300;">The Answer</div>
              <div style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--copper-bright);line-height:1.4;font-style:italic;">Health Discovery. The most valuable assessment of an individual's physiological health.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="applications-section">
    <div class="section-tag" data-reveal>Clinical Applications</div>
    <h2 class="display-h3" data-reveal data-delay="1">Where thermography<br><em>makes a difference.</em></h2>
    <div class="applications-grid">
      <div class="app-card" data-reveal data-delay="1"><div class="app-icon">✦</div><div class="app-title">Breast Health</div><p class="app-desc">One of the most established applications. Thermal imaging detects vascular and metabolic changes in breast tissue — a valuable, radiation-free adjunct to other assessment methods.</p></div>
      <div class="app-card" data-reveal data-delay="2"><div class="app-icon">✦</div><div class="app-title">Musculoskeletal & Pain</div><p class="app-desc">Identifies inflammation and nerve involvement in joints, muscles, and soft tissue. Powerful for chronic pain assessment, sports injury monitoring, and evaluating treatment effectiveness.</p></div>
      <div class="app-card" data-reveal data-delay="3"><div class="app-icon">✦</div><div class="app-title">Vascular Patterns</div><p class="app-desc">Circulation changes produce distinctive thermal signatures. Thermography can surface early vascular abnormalities, peripheral circulation issues, and asymmetries warranting investigation.</p></div>
      <div class="app-card" data-reveal data-delay="1"><div class="app-icon">✦</div><div class="app-title">Neurological Assessment</div><p class="app-desc">The autonomic nervous system regulates surface temperature. Nerve involvement, sympathetic activity changes, and peripheral neuropathy patterns all leave visible thermal signatures.</p></div>
      <div class="app-card" data-reveal data-delay="2"><div class="app-icon">✦</div><div class="app-title">Thyroid & Metabolic</div><p class="app-desc">Thyroid dysfunction, metabolic imbalances, and hormonal shifts can produce measurable thermal changes — useful in functional and integrative metabolic evaluation.</p></div>
      <div class="app-card" data-reveal data-delay="3"><div class="app-icon">✦</div><div class="app-title">Dental & TMJ</div><p class="app-desc">Thermal imaging of the head and neck reveals inflammation patterns around the jaw, sinuses, and lymph nodes — used widely by biological dentists and holistic practitioners.</p></div>
